author: app.com
title: Red Bank win about the Bucs' past, present and future
text:
MORE LITTLE SILVER – Nick Giglio’s voice was already giving out as his players gather around him near one end zone, the mass of humanity that descended on the field behind Red Bank Regional in a joyous celebration after a stunning 24-21 win over Red Bank Catholic having dispersed.
In one sense, it was about the undefeated team now kneeling on the grass, the majority of whom lost to the Caseys 53-0 last year, and those who came before them for a program that hadn’t beaten Red Bank Catholic in over a decade, and hasn’t won a state championship in 40 years.
But it was also about the people who stood five-deep on the fence and packed the grandstand, and an entire area that may finally believe that the Bucs are for real.
``In the pregame I talked to you about the power of the Buc,’’ Giglio said. ``The power of the Buc, are you kidding me? That power, those fans, those alumni, gave you that strength, and you did it.’’
They certainly did.
